What Changed in send_report.yml

Logo & Title: now in a two‚Äêcell table row, so they sit side-by-side.

Removed the ‚ÄúView Full Report‚Äù CTA row entirely.

‚ÄúValidation Failed‚Äù summary cell and detail‚Äêtable cells remain in red (#dc3545 background).

All other role files are identical to the prior implementation. This ensures a single‚Äêline header and no extraneous button, just the rich summary and detail you need.







You said:
how to run dryrun to just the check and send report 


ChatGPT said:

Thought for a couple of seconds
To exercise only the ‚Äúcheck‚Äù steps (fetching PEMs, calculating expiry, parsing configs, validating via OpenSSL/HTTP) and then send the HTML report‚Äîwithout doing any renewals, KDB imports, copies or service restarts‚Äîyou can leverage:

The report_only variable you already have in vars/main.yml

A combination of Ansible tags

Ansible‚Äôs built-in --check (dry-run) mode

1. Guard ‚Äúdestructive‚Äù tasks on report_only
Make sure all tasks that actually change state (renew, copy, import, restart) are skipped when report_only: true. For example in tasks/process_cert.yml:

yaml
Copy
Edit
- name: "Renew PFX via VCert CLI"
  when:
    - not report_only
    - cert_alias_list is defined
  ‚Ä¶
And similarly guard:

KDB creation/import

Copying PFX to servers

Backups & restores

Service restarts

So that when report_only is true, none of those ever run.

2. Tag your tasks
You already have tags on every task:

precheck ‚Üí download PEM, expiry check

extract ‚Üí parse configs

validation‚Üí SSL serial + HTTP-200 checks

report ‚Üí send_report

Ensure all actual renewal/import tasks are tagged renew or process, and none of the precheck/extract/validation/report tasks have those tags.

3. Invoke with --check, -e report_only=true, and limited tags
Run your playbook like this:

bash
Copy
Edit
ansible-playbook site.yml \
  -i inventory/hosts \
  --check \
  -e report_only=true \
  -t precheck,extract,validation,report
--check tells Ansible to simulate changes (though with our guards on report_only, even ‚Äúcheckable‚Äù modules like copy or command will be skipped).

-e report_only=true ensures all guarded tasks (when: not report_only) are skipped.

-t precheck,extract,validation,report limits the run to only the download, expiry, parsing, validation, and mail steps.

This achieves exactly a dry-run of the checks plus the final email, without touching any KDBs, httpd files, or services.

